messages.message:
Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp\n+++ b/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp\n@@ -10425,10 +10425,16 @@ StmtResult SemaOpenMP::ActOnOpenMPSimdDirective(\n   if (NestedLoopCount == 0)\n     return StmtError();\n \n-  if (finishLinearClauses(SemaRef, Clauses, B, DSAStack))\n-    return StmtError();\n+  // If loop expressions were not built, bail out early to avoid assertion failure.\n+  if (!B.builtAll())\n+    return StmtError();\n+\n+  if (finishLinearClauses(SemaRef, Clauses, B, DSAStack))\n+    return StmtError();\n \n   if (checkSimdlenSafelenSpecified(SemaRef, Clauses))\n     return StmtError();\n \n   auto *SimdDirective = OMPSimdDirective::Create(\n       getASTContext(), StartLoc, EndLoc, NestedLoopCount, Clauses, AStmt, B);\n   return SimdDirective;\n }\n'}`
responded: The root cause of the crash is that the code does not check whether the collapse clause's argument is valid before proceeding to build loop expressions. In the provided PoC, the collapse clause uses an undeclared identifier (`collapse(a)`), which leads to the loop expressions not being built, but the code still asserts that they are built.

**Patch plan:**
- In `ActOnOpenMPSimdDirective` (and similar places), after calling `checkOpenMPLoop`, if the loop expressions are not built (i.e., `B.builtAll()` is false), return an error before calling `finishLinearClauses`.
- This prevents the assertion in `finishLinearClauses` from being triggered on invalid input.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp
+++ b/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp
@@ -10425,10 +10425,16 @@ StmtResult SemaOpenMP::ActOnOpenMPSimdDirective(
   if (NestedLoopCount == 0)
     return StmtError();

-  if (finishLinearClauses(SemaRef, Clauses, B, DSAStack))
-    return StmtError();
+  // If loop expressions were not built, bail out early to avoid assertion failure.
+  if (!B.builtAll())
+    return StmtError();
+
+  if (finishLinearClauses(SemaRef, Clauses, B, DSAStack))
+    return StmtError();

   if (checkSimdlenSafelenSpecified(SemaRef, Clauses))
     return StmtError();

   auto *SimdDirective = OMPSimdDirective::Create(
       getASTContext(), StartLoc, EndLoc, NestedLoopCount, Clauses, AStmt, B);
   return SimdDirective;
 }
```

This patch ensures that if the loop expressions are not built (due to invalid or dependent collapse/ordered arguments), the function returns an error before reaching the assertion in `finishLinearClauses`. This will prevent the crash and provide a proper diagnostic for the user.

